The Edo State Government has demolished T. Latifa Hotel owned by Mr. Tony Adun also known as Kabaka, for violating building laws as the structure sits across a road in the Ugbor-Amagba axis of Oredo Local Government Area of the state. The hotel building was reduced to rubbles on Wednesday afternoon. According to the Edo government, the demolition action was executed after an injunction secured by Mr Adun against the exercise was vacated by the state government. The government said it pencilled the structure for demolition, as it was illegal, without an approved building plan for a hotel and sitting across a road. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1334648" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=458%2C611&#038;ssl=1" alt="T. Latifa Hotel owned by Mr. Tony Adun in Edo State" width="458" height="611" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=225%2C300&amp;ssl=1 225w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=44%2C58&amp;ssl=1 44w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=146%2C194&amp;ssl=1 146w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=98%2C130&amp;ssl=1 98w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?resize=560%2C747&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Edo.jpg?w=768&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> <img class="wp-image-1334649 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=466%2C621&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="466" height="621" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=225%2C300&amp;ssl=1 225w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=44%2C58&amp;ssl=1 44w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=146%2C194&amp;ssl=1 146w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=98%2C130&amp;ssl=1 98w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?resize=560%2C747&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Bulldozer.jpg?w=768&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 466px) 100vw, 466px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> “The deed of transfer being paraded by Mr. Adun is also not registered with the state government, according to court papers filed by Solicitor General of Edo State, Oluwole Iyamu SAN,” the government asserted. Bulldozers and caterpillars were mobilized to the site for the exercise while security operatives mounted guard to ensure the process was not disrupted by thugs in the area loyal to Mr Adun. The leader of the security team cordoned off the area and urged residents and shop owners around the area not to panic while the exercise lasted. However, Mr. Adun, the owner of the demolished hotel was reported to be a member of the All Progressive Congress (APC) and an adept follower of the APC National Chairman, Adams Oshiomhole. Vanguard News Nigeria. A Benin High Court has refused to grant the prayer of one Tony Kabaka Adun seeking an extension of the initial 14-day restraining order, which temporarily stopped the Edo State Government from removing his illegal building earlier marked for demolition. The court presided over by Justice D. I. Okungbowa yesterday… October 31, 2019 In "News" MEMBERS of the youth wing of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in Edo state have in the last few days been enmeshed in verbal war over the performance of the almost two years old administration of Governor Godwin Obaseki who in the eyes of non party members have performed… July 25, 2018 In "News" Youths in the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC in Edo State have joined some other party leaders to express bitterness over th